<!--
This file defines datasources (schemas, databases) for the SoftBrands HMS application:
In this file you can edit/remove connection information:
    name     - the name of the connection, has to be matched with the tenant name in the MPConfiguration.xml file
    host     - host name of the Oracle server
    port     - port number Oracle Listener is running on
    SID      - SID or service name of the Oracle DB
    user     - schema/user name
    password - schema/user access password.
    min-size - number of the connections created during application server startup
    max-size - maximum number of the connections allowed per data source.
The following is an example of the configuration for Oracle:
        <db-connection name="DS_MP_1">
            <url>jdbc:oracle:thin:@[host]:[port]:[SID]</url>
            <driver>oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver</driver>
            <user>[user]</user>
            <password>[password]</password>
            <min-size>5</min-size>
            <max-size>10</max-size>
            <idle-timeout-minutes>1</idle-timeout-minutes>
        </db-connection>
The following is an example of the configuration for Microsoft SQL server:
        <db-connection name="DS_MP_1">
            <url>jdbc:jtds:sqlserver://[host]:[port]/[database name];ProgramName=Infor;SelectMethod=cursor;useLOBs=false</url>
            <driver>net.sourceforge.jtds.jdbc.Driver</driver>
            <user>[user]</user>
            <password>[password]</password>
            <min-size>5</min-size>
            <max-size>10</max-size>
            <idle-timeout-minutes>1</idle-timeout-minutes>
        </db-connection>
*) All values specified as [....] should be replaced with installation-specific values.
-->
